## Damage-prevention vs value-preservation gates

At milestone time (after each slice merges), check BOTH axes:

- **Damage prevention:** what could this slice have broken? Specifically: the existing truth surface still works; existing concerns still pass; no regression in features the slice didn't touch.
- **Value preservation:** what value did the existing system have that this slice might have destroyed even if it "worked"? E.g., a refactor that "succeeds" but removes a useful side-effect; a migration that completes but loses a feature the old path supported.

Both axes must be cleared at each milestone. A slice that passes damage-prevention but destroys preserved value is still a failure.

